    <abstract id="aspace_0e580b63e927020f04e1527a92c409d5">Located in Macon, Georgia.  Grew out of schools for African Americans first taught in 1865.  In 1868 the American Missionary Society built a school building and named the school Lewis High School.  In 1888 a new brick building was built, a gift of Stephen Ballard and the school was renamed Ballard Normal School.  In 1949 it merged with Hudson High School to become Ballard-Hudson Senior High.</abstract>
